in the previous days. The AstraZeneca's vaccine administration restarted some days later, on March 19th, after the clarifications provided by the European Medicines Agency (EMA).

On June 10th, an 18 years-old female student died after being vaccinated with AstraZeneca 2-weeks before. After the Ligurian Sanitary Agency stops the administration for the vaccine, the Italian Government decides to follow the local decision and to stop the vaccine's administration to people under 60 years.
